Package com.rb.nonbiz.collections

Class IndexInOrderedCollection<T>

java.lang.Object
com.rb.nonbiz.collections.IndexInOrderedCollection<T>
public class IndexInOrderedCollection<T>
extends java.lang.Object
This abstraction is useful so we can ask the question "how far from the beginning and the end is a specific item in an ordered collection?". For example, if we have stocks A1, A2, A3, A4, A5 in instrument class A, then A2 has an index from the start of 1 (using array-style, 0-based indexing), and an index from the end of 3.
